HEADWORD: Dunkerque
<hw>Dunkerque</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>the name of a town and a
battle fought there, in World War II (1940) when 330,000 Allied troops
had to be evacuated from the beaches at Dunkirk in a desperate retreat
under enemy fire. Most of the forces were safely evacuated to
England.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Dunkirk.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

